Selenium
selenium - it is a webdriver automation tool, which is used to automate web based application. it is open source tool. it is platform in-dependent and also it supports multiple language.
 
 
Disadvantage - 
- it can not automate otp, images, captcha, barcodes. 
- it can not automate window based popups
- it can not automate android based application.
 
Components of selenium -
- Selenium IDE  Download as extention, attach to browser then click on record and play then execute your steps support only firefox, No programming required
- selenium RC   Multiple languages for coding
- selenium grid Multiple browsers support
- selenium Webdriver 

Locator
It used to locate web element. it is devided into 8 type
- id
- name
- tagname
- classname
- LinkText 
- partialLinkText
- CSS selector
- xpath

Note: 
id is fastest.
css is faster then xpath.

Types of xpath:
1 absolute xpath - starts with '/' and it always travers in forward direction, it is slow and static in nature because of which it is not much stable
2 relative xpath - starts with '//' and it travers in both direction, it is dynamic in nature because of which it is more stable

we use xpath majorly because it provides multiple methods which we can use to locate complex webelements easily, those methods are:
- following
- following-sibing
- starts-with
- ends-with
- preceding
- preceding-sibling
- parent
- child
- And
- Or
- Ancester
- decedent
- contains
- texts
- normalise-space

TestNg - it is a framework which is based on TDD. it is used in place of junit. it is also called as test next generation. it gives us multiple advantage like beloew.
 
1) it provides annotations with the help of which we execute our code.
  - @beforeSuit
  - @beforeTest
  - @beforeClass
  - @beforeMethod
  - @Test
  - @afterMethod
  - @afterClass
  - @afterTest
  - @afterSuit
 
2) it gives us .xml from where we connect all test classes to execute in together.
3) it give us automatically generated reports.

